      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@gmaxwell This argument is based on the situation where user has several Bitcoin Core nodes running around the world. There are other situations where user has to \"re-count\" the time in the bitcoind's `debug.log` file to compare it to the other logs from other deamons/messages/logs from his (only) system.\nMy personal preference would be to log in local time (as other services on my machines are doing) and have an option (turned off by default) to log in UTC.\n",
