      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I use `-printtoconsole` myself, yes. No need for additional option, right.\nTo paraphrase your last paragraph:\nBTW: I'd think it is much easier to correlate multiple system apps in different log files if times are in local time (as other system apps' logs already do), not UTC. If you then want to find out what happened at a certain time of the day you do not have to convert from UTC at all and look up that timestamp in all the other logs. If the bitcoind log is in UTC, that's a lot more involved.\n\nTwo use cases. We make it hard for the other one right now. And we are the only app that is doing so... At least I'm not aware of any other app doing this.\n",
