      "body" : "@paveljanik Yes, in the end everything is a compromise. The are valid reasons for logging in local time just as well, no argument there. But for the built-in logging I'd say we stick with UTC. For anything else, use external tools.\n(could take the hardline stance that `-logtimestamps` was a bad idea in the first place and we should have left tacking on timestamps to external tools, but meh, let's just stop the argument here and work on more productive things)\n",
